</p>
<p>You're witnessing the power of a special "variable system" inside config files.
Here's how it works: in any of these configuration files, you can have a
<code>parameters</code> key. And below that you can create variables like <code>locale</code> and set that
to a value. Why is this cool? Because you can then reuse that value in <em>any</em> other file
by saying <code>%locale%</code>. </p>
<p>Look under the <code>doctrine</code> key:</p>
