</p>
<p>Run over in the terminal to see if the parameter showed up:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./bin/console debug:container --parameters</div></code></pre>
<p>It's right on top. Cool! Clear the cache in the <code>prod</code> environment so we can double-check
everything is still working:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./bin/console cache:clear --env=prod</div></code></pre>
<p>Ok good - now refresh using <code>app.php</code>. It's still loading fast - so we haven't
broken anything... yet.</p>
<p>Here's where things get interesting. In <code>config_dev.yml</code>, it took a lot of code <em>just</em>
to turn caching off. Parameters to the rescue! Copy the <code>parameters</code> key from <code>config.yml</code>
and paste it into this file. But now, change its value to <code>array</code> and celebrate
by completely removing the <code>doctrine_cache</code> key at the bottom:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="f2d1f0d367">
